gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pelicans 139, Raptors 98
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pelicans shot 24-49 from beyond the arc as they defeated the Raptors, 139-98. Trey Murphy III led New Orleans with 34 points (11-17 FG) as he tied a career-high in 3PM by shooting 10-14 from distance. Brandon Ingram added 16 points, eight rebounds, and nine assists in the win. Immanuel Quickley led the Raptors with 17 points, seven rebounds, and seven assists. New Orleans improves to 37-25 as the Raptors move to 23-39.
